OL,6,FMr Taylor said it was a credit to the
OL,7,Fprison's governor that "most
OL,8,Frelationships between staff and
OL,9,Fchildren were relatively positive
OL,10,Fcompared with other YOIs", but added:
OL,11,F"It was scarcely credible in a jail
OL,12,Fholding just 165 children with 24
OL,13,Fsenior managers and 67 other managers
OL,14,Fthat leaders told us they could not
OL,15,Fgive children frequent, structured
OL,16,Fcontact with staff because of a
OL,17,Fshortage of officers."
