OL,7,FSouza said she was "appalled" by the
OL,8,Ffindings and she had written to
OL,9,FJustice Secretary Alex Chalk to ask
OL,10,Fhow conditions are being improved,
OL,11,Fadding that too many children were
OL,12,Fbeing "incarcerated rather than cared
OL,13,Ffor".
OL,15,FStrip search is an "intrusive and
OL,16,Fpotentially traumatic power" and
OL,17,Fshould "never" be carried out on
OL,18,Fchildren by a member of the opposite
OL,19,Fsex, she said.
